        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 3 at 2:51PM EDT by NWS Burlington VT</headline>
        <description>At 250 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms over Hammond Village, moving southeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hammond Village, Morristown Village, Richville, Gouverneur Village,
De Peyster, Gouverneur, Macomb, Rossie, De Kalb, Fowler, Hammond,
Morristown, Hermon, Oswegatchie, Canton, Chippewa Bay, Jacques
Cartier State Park, Edwardsville, North Gouverneur, and West Fowler.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
